The evidence with the title 'Health costs: how the U.S. compares with other countries | pbs ... ' says Oct 22, 2012  ... How much is good health care worth to you ? $8,233 per year? That's how much the U.S. spends per person . Worth it? That figure is more than two-and-a-half times more than most developed nations in the world , including relatively rich European countries like France , Sweden and the United Kingdom. 
